SSO Rajasthan (Single Sign-On) is a digital portal created by the Government of Rajasthan to provide citizens, business owners, and government employees with a single point of access for over 100+ government services.
Instead of having different usernames and passwords for every department, you use one SSO ID to access everything from job applications to utility bills.
Key Services Available
The portal acts as a gateway to several major Rajasthan government platforms, including:
e-Mitra: Access to various certificates (birth, caste, income) and public services.
Recruitment Portal: Apply for government jobs (RPSC, RSMSSB) and track application status.
Jan Aadhaar: Manage family identity and welfare benefits.Scholarships: 

Apply for student scholarship schemes.
Utility Bills: Pay electricity, water, and landline bills online.
Business Services: GST registration, labor department filings, and building plan approvals.

How to Get StartedTo use these services, you must register on the official portal: sso.rajasthan.gov.in.
Category Registration Requiremen tCitizens Use Jan Aadhaar card, Aadhaar card, or Google/Facebook account.
Businesses (Udyog)Use Business Registration Number (BRN) or Udyog Aadhaar.
Govt EmployeesUse State Insurance and Provident Fund (SIPF) ID.
Why It Matters
Convenience: One login for everythingâ€”no need to remember multiple passwords.
Transparency: You can track the real-time status of your applications and documents.
Accessibility: Available through the web portal or the "SSO Raj" mobile app on Android.
